---
import RunsBadge from "../components/RunsBadge.astro";
import DiagramBox from "../components/DiagramBox.astro";
import Callout from "../components/Callout.astro";
---

<div class="space-y-8">
  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-zinc-300">
    You've now seen every piece individually. Here's how they all fit together.
    Regardless of which specific tools you pick, the modern web stack follows
    the same fundamental pattern: code is
    <strong class="text-blue-300">authored</strong> on a dev machine,
    <strong class="text-blue-300">built</strong> into optimized output,
    <strong class="text-blue-300">served</strong> to browsers, and
    <strong class="text-blue-300">connected</strong> to backend services.
  </p>

  {/* Main architecture diagram */}
  <DiagramBox class="!border-blue-800/40 !bg-blue-950/10">
    <div class="text-center mb-6">
      <span class="text-xs font-mono text-zinc-400 uppercase tracking-widest">
        The Modern Web Architecture
      </span>
    </div>

    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      {/* Dev Machine */}
      <div
        class="rounded-2xl border-2 border-cyan-700/50 bg-zinc-950/80 p-5 space-y-4"
      >
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-1">
          <span class="text-2xl">🖥️</span>
          <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-cyan-300">Development</h3>
        </div>
        <RunsBadge location="Your Machine" color="cyan" />
        <div class="space-y-2 text-sm">
          <div class="rounded-lg bg-cyan-950/30 border border-cyan-900/30 p-3">
            <div class="font-mono text-xs text-cyan-300 font-bold">
              JS Runtime
            </div>
            <div class="text-zinc-400 text-xs mt-0.5">
              Node.js / Bun — runs your dev tools
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="text-cyan-600 text-center">▾</div>
          <div class="rounded-lg bg-cyan-950/30 border border-cyan-900/30 p-3">
            <div class="font-mono text-xs text-cyan-300 font-bold">
              Bundler + Dev Server
            </div>
            <div class="text-zinc-400 text-xs mt-0.5">
              Vite / Webpack — bundles code, HMR
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="text-cyan-600 text-center">▾</div>
          <div class="rounded-lg bg-cyan-950/30 border border-cyan-900/30 p-3">
            <div class="font-mono text-xs text-cyan-300 font-bold">
              Build-Time Tools
            </div>
            <div class="text-zinc-400 text-xs mt-0.5">
              TypeScript, Tailwind, ESLint
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div
          class="text-xs text-zinc-500 font-mono pt-2 border-t border-cyan-900/20"
        >
          npm run dev → localhost:5173
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* Production / Static Host */}
      <div class="space-y-6">
        {/* Build output */}
        <div
          class="rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-700/50 bg-zinc-950/80 p-5 space-y-3"
        >
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-1">
            <span class="text-2xl">📦</span>
            <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-amber-300">Build Output</h3>
          </div>
          <RunsBadge location="Build Step / CI" color="amber" />
          <p class="text-xs text-zinc-400">
            <code class="text-amber-300">npm run build</code> produces optimized static
            files:
          </p>
          <div class="space-y-1">
            {
              ["index.html", "assets/app.ab3f.js", "assets/style.c9.css"].map(
                (f) => (
                  <div class="font-mono text-xs text-amber-200/80 bg-amber-950/30 rounded px-2 py-1">
                    dist/{f}
                  </div>
                ),
              )
            }
          </div>
          <div
            class="text-xs text-zinc-500 font-mono pt-2 border-t border-amber-900/20"
          >
            Deployed to a CDN or static host
          </div>
        </div>

        {/* Arrow */}
        <div class="flex justify-center">
          <div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-1 text-zinc-500">
            <span class="text-xs font-mono">served to</span>
            <span class="text-2xl">⬇</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        {/* Browser */}
        <div
          class="rounded-2xl border-2 border-violet-700/50 bg-zinc-950/80 p-5 space-y-3"
        >
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-1">
            <span class="text-2xl">🌐</span>
            <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-violet-300">
              User's Browser
            </h3>
          </div>
          <RunsBadge location="User's Browser" color="violet" />
          <div class="space-y-2 text-sm">
            <div
              class="rounded-lg bg-violet-950/30 border border-violet-900/30 p-3"
            >
              <div class="font-mono text-xs text-violet-300 font-bold">
                Frontend Framework
              </div>
              <div class="text-zinc-400 text-xs mt-0.5">
                React / Vue / Svelte — builds & updates UI
              </div>
            </div>
            <div
              class="rounded-lg bg-violet-950/30 border border-violet-900/30 p-3"
            >
              <div class="font-mono text-xs text-violet-300 font-bold">
                Client Libraries
              </div>
              <div class="text-zinc-400 text-xs mt-0.5">
                TanStack Query, router, state management
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* Backend Server */}
      <div
        class="rounded-2xl border-2 border-emerald-700/50 bg-zinc-950/80 p-5 space-y-4"
      >
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-1">
          <span class="text-2xl">⚙️</span>
          <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-emerald-300">
            Backend Server
          </h3>
        </div>
        <RunsBadge location="Server / Cloud" color="emerald" />
        <div class="space-y-2 text-sm">
          <div
            class="rounded-lg bg-emerald-950/30 border border-emerald-900/30 p-3"
          >
            <div class="font-mono text-xs text-emerald-300 font-bold">
              API Endpoints
            </div>
            <div class="text-zinc-400 text-xs mt-0.5">
              REST or GraphQL — your app's interface
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="text-emerald-600 text-center">▾</div>
          <div
            class="rounded-lg bg-emerald-950/30 border border-emerald-900/30 p-3"
          >
            <div class="font-mono text-xs text-emerald-300 font-bold">
              Business Logic
            </div>
            <div class="text-zinc-400 text-xs mt-0.5">
              Auth, validation, processing
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="text-emerald-600 text-center">▾</div>
          <div
            class="rounded-lg bg-emerald-950/30 border border-emerald-900/30 p-3"
          >
            <div class="font-mono text-xs text-emerald-300 font-bold">
              Database
            </div>
            <div class="text-zinc-400 text-xs mt-0.5">
              PostgreSQL, MongoDB, Redis, etc.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div
          class="text-xs text-zinc-500 font-mono pt-2 border-t border-emerald-900/20"
        >
          Can be any language: JS, Python, Go, Rust...
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    {/* Connection arrows */}
    <div class="mt-6 pt-4 border-t border-zinc-800">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-6 text-xs font-mono">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <div class="w-8 border-t-2 border-violet-500"></div>
          <span class="text-violet-400">
            Browser &harr; Server communicate via HTTP (JSON)
          </span>
          <div class="w-8 border-t-2 border-emerald-500"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </DiagramBox>

  {/* Key principles */}
  <div class="space-y-4">
    <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-blue-300 text-xl">
      Core Principles (No Matter What You Pick)
    </h3>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      {
        [
          {
            title: "Separation of Concerns",
            desc: "Each layer has one job. The bundler builds. The framework renders. The server stores data. Swap any piece without rewriting the rest.",
            icon: "🧩",
          },
          {
            title: "Build vs Runtime",
            desc: "Some tools run once at build time (TypeScript, Tailwind, bundler) and some run every time a user visits (React, TanStack Query, your API). Knowing which is which avoids confusion.",
            icon: "⏱️",
          },
          {
            title: "Client vs Server",
            desc: "The browser is the client. Your API is the server. They communicate over HTTP with JSON. The browser can't access databases; the server can't access the DOM.",
            icon: "🔀",
          },
          {
            title: "Static vs Dynamic",
            desc: "Some content never changes (CSS, images, compiled JS) and can be served from a CDN. Dynamic content (user data, personalized pages) requires a server.",
            icon: "📄",
          },
        ].map((p) => (
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-blue-900/30 bg-blue-950/10 p-4">
            <div class="text-2xl mb-2">{p.icon}</div>
            <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-blue-300 mb-1">{p.title}</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">{p.desc}</p>
          </div>
        ))
      }
    </div>
  </div>

  {/* Common stacks */}
  <div class="space-y-4">
    <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-blue-300 text-xl">
      Common Stacks in the Wild
    </h3>
    <div class="space-y-3">
      {
        [
          {
            name: "Vite + React + Separate API",
            tags: ["CSR", "Headless"],
            desc: "Frontend is static files on a CDN. Backend is a separate server (Express, Django, Go, etc). Simplest architecture. Great for SPAs and dashboards.",
            color: "#a78bfa",
          },
          {
            name: "Next.js (Full-stack)",
            tags: ["SSR", "SSG", "API Routes"],
            desc: "One codebase handles both frontend and backend. Server components fetch data, API routes handle mutations. Popular for public-facing apps.",
            color: "#2dd4bf",
          },
          {
            name: "Astro + Headless CMS",
            tags: ["SSG", "Islands"],
            desc: "Mostly static HTML generated at build time. Interactive React/Vue components only where needed. Ideal for content sites, blogs, and docs.",
            color: "#fbbf24",
          },
          {
            name: "React Native / Expo",
            tags: ["Mobile", "Cross-platform"],
            desc: "Same React concepts, but renders to native iOS/Android instead of the DOM. Still talks to a backend API the same way.",
            color: "#fb7185",
          },
        ].map((stack) => (
          <div
            class="rounded-xl border p-4 flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4"
            style={`border-color: ${stack.color}25; background-color: ${stack.color}06;`}
          >
            <div class="sm:w-64 flex-shrink-0">
              <div
                class="font-display font-bold"
                style={`color: ${stack.color};`}
              >
                {stack.name}
              </div>
              <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1.5 mt-1.5">
                {stack.tags.map((tag) => (
                  <span
                    class="text-[10px] font-mono font-bold uppercase tracking-wider px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full"
                    style={`color: ${stack.color}; background-color: ${stack.color}15;`}
                  >
                    {tag}
                  </span>
                ))}
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">{stack.desc}</p>
          </div>
        ))
      }
    </div>
  </div>

  <Callout color="#60a5fa" icon="🚀">
    <strong class="text-blue-300">The typical dev workflow:</strong>
    <ol class="mt-2 space-y-1 text-zinc-400 list-decimal list-inside">
      <li>
        Write components in your framework of choice + style with Tailwind or
        CSS
      </li>
      <li>
        <code class="text-cyan-300 text-xs">npm run dev</code> — bundler serves your
        app locally with HMR
      </li>
      <li>Your app runs in the browser, fetches data from an API</li>
      <li>
        <code class="text-amber-300 text-xs">npm run build</code> — TypeScript checks,
        Tailwind compiles, bundler optimizes
      </li>
      <li>Deploy — static files to a CDN, or a server for SSR</li>
    </ol>
  </Callout>

  <div
    class="rounded-2xl border border-blue-800/30 bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-950/20 to-violet-950/20 p-6 text-center space-y-3"
  >
    <div class="text-3xl">🎓</div>
    <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-blue-200">
      You now understand the modern web stack.
    </h3>
    <p class="text-zinc-400 max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
      Every piece has a clear role and a clear place where it runs. The package
      manager downloads libraries to your machine. The bundler builds on your
      machine. TypeScript and Tailwind run at build time. The framework runs in
      the browser (or on the server, for SSR). Your API runs on a server. Data
      flows between them via HTTP.
      <strong class="text-zinc-300">
        The specific tools change — the architecture doesn't.
      </strong>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
